description:
&lt;p&gt;The Campaigns and Public Affairs Manager will join the communications department at an exciting time for Mid and South Essex NHS Foundation Trust as a newly formed acute trust, and one of the largest in England.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our communications and engagement department supports the strategic priorities of the Trust through the delivery of excellent communications focused on our patients, staff and wider communities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Campaigns and Public Affairs team provides guidance and advice for programmes and directorates on the external stakeholder landscape and how to secure support for our work. They are responsible for devising an executing creative campaign strategies that support the Trust’s objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team also manages relationships with a diverse range of national, local and regional stakeholders, gathering intelligence on external events and publications, and are responsible for communicating service changes and reconfiguration plans to external audiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameEsther KukuJob titleHead of Campaigns and Public AffairsEmail addressesther.kuku@btuh.nhs.ukTelephone number01268 524900 ext 2993&lt;/p&gt;
